.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:34:6. **Coding style** — TypeScript best practices, error-handling patterns, type-safety gaps (any, unknown misuse, non-null assertions), async correctness
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:82:- **content** — Content to review: diff, spec, story, doc, or any artifact
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:378:A production-readiness overhaul of the EyeMatics Clinical Demonstrator (EMD), a React/TypeScript clinical research dashboard for ophthalmological IVOM treatment data. The redesign adds a standalone Express backend, optional Keycloak OIDC authentication (with local credential fallback), server-side audit logging, center-based data restriction, and migrates all persistent state from localStorage to server-side JSON file storage.
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:405:- [x] Server-side audit log (append-only SQLite, replaces localStorage) — v1.0 (Phase 2)
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:417:- [x] Frontend DataContext wired to server /api/data/* endpoints (no localStorage) — v1.1
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:469:- [ ] metricSelector integration tests — `describe.skip` placeholder; needs full router context
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:573:| All localStorage to server | Audit compliance requires it; partial migration creates inconsistent patterns | ✓ Complete — audit (Phase 2), data persistence (Phase 4) |
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:583:| Cohort ID hashed in audit events (v1.6) | HMAC-SHA256 truncated to 16 hex chars. Secret in settings.yaml. hashCohortId reused by aggregation audit event. URL stays clean (no querystring PII). | ✓ Validated — closes CRREV-01 / IN-01 |
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:656:- [ ] **AGG-01**: New `POST /api/outcomes/aggregate` endpoint accepts `{ cohortId, axisMode, yMetric, gridPoints, eye }` and returns `{ median, iqrLow, iqrHigh, perPatient?, scatter? }` — center-filtered from JWT, not from request body.
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:659:- [ ] **AGG-04**: Server aggregation response is cacheable per `{ cohortId, axisMode, yMetric, gridPoints, eye }` key with explicit cache invalidation on cohort mutation (ETag or in-memory TTL — chosen during plan phase).
.planning/reviews/v1.7-full-review/codex.stdout:675:- [ ] **CRREV-01** (IN-01): Audit beacon `GET /api/audit/events/view-open` no longer carries cohort id in querystring; cohort reference sent as hashed id in the event payload, verified by test against the audit DB row.
