.planning/RETROSPECTIVE.md:22:- **TDD RED-scaffold pattern**: Wave 0 created `describe.skip` RED tests that Wave 1 activated — prevented test drift and gave each plan a clear acceptance surface
.planning/RETROSPECTIVE.md:51:- Notable: Wave-based parallel execution with 5 worktree agents was the most efficient approach; plan quality gates (gsd-plan-checker) caught 2 BLOCKERs before any code was written
.planning/ROADMAP.md:51:  2. On a fresh deployment, `data/cohort-hash-secret.txt` is auto-created at startup; the `audit.cohortHashSecret` fallback value in `settings.yaml` is no longer consulted for that field
.planning/ROADMAP.md:52:  3. A user whose record carries the default migrated password `changeme2025!` is redirected to a forced password-change flow on their next login; they cannot access any other route until the change is complete
.planning/ROADMAP.md:69:  2. After TOTP enrollment, `POST /verify` accepts only a valid RFC 6238 TOTP code (±1 window); the site-wide static `otpCode` from `settings.yaml` is no longer accepted for that user
.planning/ROADMAP.md:105:  1. The audit log page has a user dropdown, an action-category filter (Auth / Data / Admin / Outcomes), a date-range picker, a cohort-hash text search field, and a failures-only toggle; applying any filter updates the displayed log without a page reload
.planning/ROADMAP.md:109:  5. Theme preference survives page reload (stored in `localStorage`); when set to System, the preference tracks `prefers-color-scheme` media query changes; there is no flash of unstyled content on load
