.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-04-PLAN.md:300:    - When `cohort.cases.length > threshold`: a `useEffect` triggers THREE parallel `postAggregate` calls (one each for eye='od', 'os', 'combined') keyed on (cohortId, axisMode, yMetric, gridPoints, spreadMode, layers.perPatient, layers.scatter). The three responses are reassembled into a `TrajectoryResult`-shaped object whose `PanelResult` values are constructed from the server's `{median, iqrLow, iqrHigh, perPatient?, scatter?, meta}` projections. This assembled object feeds the existing `aggregate` variable (same consumers unchanged).
.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-04-PLAN.md:302:    - On server error (any non-200): `console.warn('[OutcomesView] Server aggregate failed — falling back to client compute', err)`, then fall through to the existing client useMemo path. No user-visible red error; the chart renders as if server mode weren't active.
.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-04-PLAN.md:303:    - No route without `cohortId` (ad-hoc filter path) ever calls the server — `postAggregate` requires a cohortId. For ad-hoc filters above threshold, the client path runs unchanged.
