.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-04-PLAN.md:568:    IMPORTANT: the cohort must have a matching saved-search entry in `useData().savedSearches` because OutcomesView resolves cohortId via `savedSearches.find(s => s.id === cohortId)`. Either seed that entry through the provider OR pass the cohortId as a `?filter=` param (ad-hoc path) — but ad-hoc filter path SKIPS server routing (requires a cohortId, not a filter). So you MUST seed the saved search. The existing OutcomesPage tests already do this — mirror their setup.
