.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-02-SUMMARY.md:49:  - "Inline re-implementation of extractPatientCases + applyFilters + getAge in server/outcomesAggregateApi.ts rather than importing from src/services/fhirLoader.ts. The plan's <interfaces> block prescribes exactly this pivot when the fhirLoader import transitively fails: src/services/fhirLoader.ts imports authFetch from src/services/authHeaders.ts which references sessionStorage/window. Node runtime imports succeed (tested) but tsconfig.server.json compiles with lib:[ES2023] (no DOM), so TS fails to declare window/sessionStorage. Reimplementing the 40-line surface locally against shared/ imports keeps the server build self-contained and matches fhirLoader.ts semantics line-for-line."
.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-02-SUMMARY.md:149:$ grep -qE "JSON\.stringify\([^)]*cohortId\b" server/outcomesAggregateApi.ts ; echo "exit=$?"
.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-02-SUMMARY.md:150:exit=1                                                                          # ✓ T-12-04: no raw cohortId in any stringify literal
.planning/phases/12-server-side-outcomes-pre-aggregation/12-02-SUMMARY.md:176:Mitigation locked: handler reads center list only from `req.auth!.centers`.
