.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-RESEARCH.md:266:- **Logging raw `cohortId` anywhere** — middleware normally stores `req.body` for POST routes (`auditMiddleware.ts:134`). The skip-list must fire BEFORE the body-capture code path, not after, or the middleware's `logAuditEntry` call will still run with the raw body in hand.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-RESEARCH.md:268:- **Hashing inside the client** — explicitly rejected in CONTEXT.md deferred list. Client code must send the raw cohortId in the POST body; server hashes.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-RESEARCH.md:286:**What goes wrong:** Middleware reads and serialises `req.body` for the POST beacon (raw cohortId included) before the skip-list fires. Even if no row is written, a raw-id leak can appear in debug logs or stack traces.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-RESEARCH.md:289:**Warning signs:** Tests that grep for the raw cohort id in any captured log output still find matches even though the DB row is correct.
