.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-CONTEXT.md:9:Cohort identifiers stop leaking into audit URLs. The view-open beacon is refactored so (a) no cohort id appears in the request URL or querystring, (b) the audit row records the cohort reference as a hashed id in the event payload, and (c) a reusable `hashCohortId(id)` utility is established and unit-tested so Phase 12's AGG-05 audit event can reuse it without duplication.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-CONTEXT.md:19:- **D-01:** Switch `/api/audit/events/view-open` from `GET` to `POST`. Client sends JSON body `{ name, cohortId?, filter? }`. No cohort or filter in the URL.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-CONTEXT.md:30:- **D-08:** Move `filter` payload off the URL into the same POST body alongside cohortId. No hashing — filter is an ad-hoc criteria snapshot, not an identifier. D-11 middleware body redaction does NOT apply here (see D-11 below).
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-CONTEXT.md:33:- **D-09:** Beacon handler is the audit row writer. It computes `cohortHash` via `hashCohortId(cohortId)`, constructs the event payload `{ name, cohortHash, filter }`, calls `logAuditEntry()` directly, then returns 204.
.planning/phases/11-audit-beacon-pii-hardening/11-CONTEXT.md:35:- **D-11:** Raw `cohortId` is never written to `audit_log.body` or `audit_log.query`. Unit test seeds a cohort, fires the beacon, reads the audit DB row, asserts `cohortHash` present AND raw id absent.
