.planning/phases/16-cross-cohort-comparison/16-REVIEW.md:45:**Issue:** The `loginDemoHint` key embeds live demo passwords (`admin2025!`, `forscher2025!`) and a fixed OTP code (`123456`) in both `de` and `en` locales. These strings are compiled into every production bundle shipped to users. If the demo environment shares infrastructure or credentials with any staging/production system, or if the credentials are reused elsewhere, this constitutes a credential exposure. Even in a fully isolated demo, shipping credentials in the bundle allows any user who inspects the JS to extract them without accessing the login UI.
.planning/phases/16-cross-cohort-comparison/16-REVIEW.md:63://   admin / admin2025! · forscher1 / forscher2025! · OTP: 123456
