.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:13:2. **Dark mode** — A sun/moon/system theme toggle in the sidebar footer switches the entire application between Light, Dark, and System modes. The `dark` CSS class on `<html>` triggers full-app Tailwind `dark:` variants. All Recharts chart internals use explicit colors from a `useTheme()` hook. Theme persists in `localStorage` with no flash of unstyled content on load.
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:15:Out of scope: any new audit write paths, pagination UI (single server-filtered fetch suffices), changes to the existing `isRelevantEntry()` noise filter semantics, new chart types or metrics.
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:61:- **D-11:** Theme preference stored in `localStorage` key `emd-theme`. `ThemeContext` reads it on mount and applies the `dark` class to `document.documentElement`. `System` mode listens to `prefers-color-scheme` changes via `addEventListener('change', ...)`.
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:65:- **D-12:** An inline `<script>` block added to `index.html` `<head>` (before any CSS or JS loads) reads `localStorage.getItem('emd-theme')` and applies `document.documentElement.classList.add('dark')` synchronously if the stored preference is `'dark'`, or if the preference is `'system'` and `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches`. This eliminates the flash of unstyled content before React hydrates.
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:72:- i18n keys for new toggle tooltip labels (Light/Dark/System) and any new audit filter labels
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:114:- **Single config source**: settings are in `settings.yaml`; theme preference is client-only → `localStorage` is the right store (not `settings.yaml`)
.planning/phases/17-audit-log-upgrade-dark-mode/17-CONTEXT.md:139:- Per-user theme preference synced server-side — localStorage is sufficient for this phase
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:9:Phase 15 replaces the shared static `otpCode` in `settings.yaml` with per-user RFC 6238 TOTP secrets using `otplib@13.4.0`. Each `UserRecord` gains three new optional fields (`totpSecret`, `totpEnabled`, `totpRecoveryCodes`). The existing `POST /verify` static comparison is replaced with a conditional: enrolled users verify against TOTP + recovery codes, non-enrolled users fall back to the static OTP. The enrollment flow follows the Phase 14 `PasswordChangePage` pattern precisely — a purpose-checked JWT gates a full-page interstitial (`TotpEnrollPage`), which is rendered by `AppRoutes()` before the router.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:141:          static otpCode comparison (unchanged fallback)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:270:**What goes wrong:** Recovery codes are 8+ chars (`ABCD-1234` = 9 chars with dash). The existing OTP input has `maxLength={6}` and `placeholder="123456"`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:274:**How to avoid:** Remove the `maxLength={6}` constraint or increase it to handle recovery codes (up to 9 chars for `XXXX-XXXX` format). Backend distinguishes TOTP vs recovery by length/format before trying bcrypt. Alternatively: `maxLength={9}` covers both. Update the `placeholder` to something like `"123456 or recovery code"`.
