.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-03-PLAN.md:65:Build the frontend enrollment experience: a full-page `TotpEnrollPage` (mirroring `PasswordChangePage`), a `RecoveryCodesPanel` that displays the 10 recovery codes with copy/download/checkbox gate, the `AuthContext` state and functions that drive enrollment, the App.tsx gate, the LoginPage OTP-length relaxation, and the 20 new i18n keys from 15-UI-SPEC.md.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-03-PLAN.md:67:Purpose: Phase 15 is invisible to users without this plan. After Plan 02 landed the backend, this plan delivers the enrollment UX so a user under `twoFactorEnabled=true` can actually enroll, see recovery codes, save them, and reach the main app.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-03-PLAN.md:68:Output: 2 new files (TotpEnrollPage, RecoveryCodesPanel), 4 modified files (AuthContext, App, LoginPage, translations).
