.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:64:**POST /totp/enroll** — validates enrollToken, generates QR via `QRCode.toDataURL(generateURI(...))`, re-issues fresh token (resets 3-min TTL).
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:66:**POST /totp/confirm** — verifies TOTP via `verifySync({epochTolerance: 30})`, generates 10 recovery codes via `Promise.all(rawCodes.map(c => bcrypt.hash(c, 12)))`, writes `totpEnabled=true` + hashes to users.json, sets `res.locals.auditAction = 'totp-enrolled'`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:69:- For enrolled users: try TOTP first (wrapped in try/catch for non-6-digit inputs), then concurrent `Promise.all` over `bcrypt.compare` for recovery codes
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:70:- Burned recovery code removed atomically inside `modifyUsers()` callback (T-15-16)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:71:- `res.locals.auditAction = 'totp-recovery-used'` on recovery path
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:74:**DELETE /users/:username/totp** — admin-only (403 for non-admin), clears `totpSecret`/`totpEnabled`/`totpRecoveryCodes` via `delete` on spread copy, sets `res.locals.auditAction = 'totp-reset'`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:79:npx vitest run tests/totpEnrollment.test.ts tests/totpAdmin.test.ts
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:97:**1. [Rule 3 - Blocking] otplib 13.4.0 functional API — no `authenticator` namespace**
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:99:- **Issue:** The plan and RESEARCH.md assumed `import { authenticator } from 'otplib'` with `authenticator.generateSecret()`, `authenticator.check()`, `authenticator.keyuri()`. In otplib 13.4.0 there is no `authenticator` export. The package exports a functional API: `generateSecret()`, `generateSync({secret})`, `verifySync({secret, token, epochTolerance})`, `generateURI({issuer, label, secret})`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:101:- **Impact:** `verifySync` throws `'Token must be 6 digits, got N'` for non-6-digit inputs (e.g. recovery codes). Wrapped in try/catch before the recovery code fallback branch.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:102:- **Files modified:** server/authApi.ts, tests/totpEnrollment.test.ts
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:106:- **Found during:** Task 1 (running full test suite revealed mustChangePassword.test.ts failures)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:107:- **Issue:** `_migrateUsersJson` was not exported from `server/initAuth.ts`, causing `mustChangePassword.test.ts` to fail with `TypeError: _migrateUsersJson is not a function`. Additionally, the function did not implement the SEC-03 logic of setting `mustChangePassword=true` for users with the default `changeme2025!` password hash — the tests expected this behavior.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:108:- **Fix:** Exported `_migrateUsersJson`; added `bcrypt.compareSync(DEFAULT_PASSWORD, user.passwordHash)` scan to set `mustChangePassword: true` for users with the default hash (unless already cleared to `false`).
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:112:**3. [Rule 3 - Blocking] Test timeouts for /totp/confirm (bcrypt×10 at rounds=12)**
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:115:- **Fix:** Added `30000` as third argument to affected `it()` calls (tests calling POST /totp/confirm).
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-02-SUMMARY.md:116:- **Files modified:** tests/totpEnrollment.test.ts
