.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:9:Phase 15 replaces the shared static `otpCode` in `settings.yaml` with per-user RFC 6238 TOTP secrets using `otplib@13.4.0`. Each `UserRecord` gains three new optional fields (`totpSecret`, `totpEnabled`, `totpRecoveryCodes`). The existing `POST /verify` static comparison is replaced with a conditional: enrolled users verify against TOTP + recovery codes, non-enrolled users fall back to the static OTP. The enrollment flow follows the Phase 14 `PasswordChangePage` pattern precisely — a purpose-checked JWT gates a full-page interstitial (`TotpEnrollPage`), which is rendered by `AppRoutes()` before the router.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:11:All decisions have been pre-made in CONTEXT.md. The implementation is a direct extension of existing Phase 14 patterns with no novel architecture. The key risk areas are: (1) correct `otplib` ESM import syntax in a `"type": "module"` project, (2) redacting `enrollToken` and `totpSecret` in the audit middleware, and (3) ensuring new TOTP API routes are added to `PUBLIC_PATHS` in `authMiddleware.ts`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:13:**Primary recommendation:** Follow the Phase 14 `mustChangePassword` / `PasswordChangePage` pattern exactly — same JWT purpose-check gate, same App.tsx interstitial, same `modifyUsers()` write pattern. The codebase already has all the structural primitives.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:24:- **D-01:** Post-password-success gate: return `{ requiresTotpEnrollment: true, enrollToken: <3-min JWT, purpose='totp-enroll'> }` instead of session token for unenrolled users when `twoFactorEnabled: true`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:25:- **D-02:** Full-page `TotpEnrollPage` (same pattern as `PasswordChangePage`) with QR code, manual key, 6-digit confirmation field
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:26:- **D-03:** 10 recovery codes, 8 alphanumeric chars (`ABCD-1234` format), bcrypt-hashed in `totpRecoveryCodes[]`, burned on use, shown once with copy-all + download-as-txt, "I have saved" checkbox gate
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:27:- **D-04:** Admin "Reset 2FA" button in AdminPage user row (visible when `totpEnabled === true`); API: `DELETE /api/auth/users/:username/totp`; clears `totpSecret`, `totpEnabled`, `totpRecoveryCodes`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:28:- **D-05:** LoginPage OTP step unchanged structurally; backend distinguishes TOTP vs recovery codes transparently
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:29:- **D-06:** `POST /verify` tries TOTP first; if fail, checks recovery codes (bcrypt.compareSync each); on recovery code match: burn it, issue JWT, include `{ recoveryCodeUsed: true }`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:31:- **D-08:** New `UserRecord` fields: `totpSecret?: string`, `totpEnabled?: boolean`, `totpRecoveryCodes?: string[]`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:32:- **D-09:** `otplib@13.4.0` + `qrcode@1.5.4`; `Authenticator.options.window = 1` (±1 period)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:34:- **D-11:** New endpoints: `POST /api/auth/totp/enroll`, `POST /api/auth/totp/confirm`, `DELETE /api/auth/users/:username/totp`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:35:- **D-12:** Audit events: `totp-enrolled`, `totp-reset`, `totp-recovery-used`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:54:| SEC-04 | TOTP (RFC 6238) per-user secret replaces site-wide static OTP; enrollment via QR code; ±1 window | `otplib@13.4.0` `authenticator` API handles RFC 6238 exactly; `qrcode.toDataURL()` generates PNG for `<img>`; `window: 1` option verified |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:55:| SEC-05 | TOTP recovery codes generated at enrollment, bcrypt-hashed per user, burned on use | `bcrypt.hashSync` + `bcrypt.compareSync` already in codebase; `modifyUsers()` removes burned code atomically |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:66:| otplib | 13.4.0 | RFC 6238 TOTP secret generation, code verification | Decided in D-09; ESM-compatible, ships CJS+ESM exports; actively maintained |
