.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:100:### Existing Pattern Being Replicated: mustChangePassword / PasswordChangePage
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:102:The Phase 14 mustChangePassword flow is the exact template. Every layer has a direct parallel:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:104:| Phase 14 (mustChangePassword) | Phase 15 (requiresTotpEnrollment) |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:106:| `{ mustChangePassword: true, changeToken }` from `/login` | `{ requiresTotpEnrollment: true, enrollToken }` from `/login` |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:107:| `purpose: 'change-password'` JWT | `purpose: 'totp-enroll'` JWT |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:108:| `mustChangePassword` state in AuthContext | `requiresTotpEnrollment` state in AuthContext |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:110:| `changePassword()` function in AuthContext | `startTotpEnroll()` + `confirmTotpEnroll()` in AuthContext |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:111:| `if (mustChangePassword) return <PasswordChangePage />` in AppRoutes | `if (requiresTotpEnrollment) return <TotpEnrollPage />` in AppRoutes |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:112:| `POST /api/auth/change-password` | `POST /api/auth/totp/enroll` + `POST /api/auth/totp/confirm` |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:120:  ├── 3. mustChangePassword gate (Phase 14 — unchanged)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:121:  ├── 4. [NEW] requiresTotpEnrollment gate:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:122:  │       if twoFactorEnabled && !user.totpEnabled
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:123:  │       → return { requiresTotpEnrollment: true, enrollToken }
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:135:        if user.totpEnabled:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:136:          a. Try TOTP: authenticator.check(otp, user.totpSecret)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:137:          b. If TOTP fails: try recovery codes (bcrypt.compareSync each)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:138:          c. If recovery code matches: burn it, flag recoveryCodeUsed=true
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:147:POST /api/auth/totp/enroll  (requires enrollToken)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:151:POST /api/auth/totp/confirm  (requires enrollToken + otp)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:153:  ├── Generate 10 recovery codes
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:154:  ├── Hash recovery codes (bcrypt, 12 rounds)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:155:  ├── modifyUsers(): set totpSecret, totpEnabled=true, totpRecoveryCodes
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:156:  ├── Audit: totp-enrolled
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:162:- **Storing plaintext recovery codes:** Store only bcrypt hashes. Never log or return codes after initial display.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:164:- **Accepting `totp-enroll` purpose tokens on protected routes:** The `verifyLocalToken` function in `authMiddleware.ts` already rejects `challenge` and `change-password` purpose tokens. `totp-enroll` must be added to the same rejection list.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:165:- **Missing PUBLIC_PATHS entries:** `/api/auth/totp/enroll` and `/api/auth/totp/confirm` must be added to `PUBLIC_PATHS` in `authMiddleware.ts` — they are gated by enrollToken, not session JWT.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:173:| TOTP code generation/verification | Custom HMAC-SHA1 + time-step math | `otplib` `authenticator` | RFC 6238 has subtle clock-skew, counter, and step-size requirements |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:176:| Atomic recovery code burn | Read-modify-write outside lock | `modifyUsers()` callback | Existing write lock prevents TOCTOU race on concurrent requests |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:178:**Key insight:** The codebase already has all needed primitives (`modifyUsers`, `bcrypt`, `jwt`, `crypto`). Only `otplib` and `qrcode` are new dependencies.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:184:### Pitfall 1: otplib ESM Import in `"type": "module"` Project
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:186:**What goes wrong:** `import { authenticator } from 'otplib'` fails at runtime or TypeScript complains about module resolution in the server context.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:188:**Why it happens:** The project uses `"type": "module"` and `tsx` for server execution. otplib 13.4.0 ships proper ESM (`dist/index.js`) and CJS (`dist/index.cjs`), so the import works — but `tsconfig.app.json` uses `moduleResolution: "bundler"` which is Vite-side only. Server code is compiled/run via `tsx` which handles ESM natively.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:190:**How to avoid:** Use the standard import `import { authenticator } from 'otplib';` in server files. Do NOT import from `otplib/presets` (legacy pattern from v11). The v13 `authenticator` object is the correct entry point.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:194:// Source: otplib 13.4.0 package exports (verified via npm view)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:195:import { authenticator } from 'otplib';
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:204:**What goes wrong:** `POST /api/auth/totp/enroll` generates a secret and returns the QR code. `POST /api/auth/totp/confirm` must verify against the SAME secret. If stored only in-memory (a Map), server restart between the two calls loses it.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:208:**How to avoid:** Sign the `totpSecret` into the `enrollToken` JWT payload itself. The JWT is already signed with the server secret, so the secret cannot be tampered with by the client. Pattern:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:211:// POST /api/auth/totp/enroll
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:214:  { sub: username, purpose: 'totp-enroll', totpSecret: secret },
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:222:// POST /api/auth/totp/confirm
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:224:  as { sub: string; purpose: string; totpSecret: string };
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:225:// payload.totpSecret is the same secret — no server-side storage needed
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:232:**What goes wrong:** Hashing 10 recovery codes at bcrypt rounds=12 during the confirmation request adds ~3-4 seconds of blocking CPU time.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:245:**What goes wrong:** `POST /verify` must check the submitted value against up to 10 hashed recovery codes, each taking ~300ms. Sequential checking can block for 3 seconds.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:252:  user.totpRecoveryCodes.map((hash) => bcrypt.compare(otp, hash))
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:256:Then burn `user.totpRecoveryCodes[matchIndex]` via `modifyUsers()`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:258:### Pitfall 5: Audit Middleware Not Redacting enrollToken and totpSecret
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:260:**What goes wrong:** `enrollToken` appears in request body for `/api/auth/totp/confirm`; `totpSecret` could appear in a logged response. Both are sensitive.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:262:**Why it happens:** `REDACT_FIELDS` in `auditMiddleware.ts` covers `password`, `otp`, `challengeToken`, `generatedPassword` — but not `enrollToken` or `totpSecret`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:265:1. Add `enrollToken` and `totpSecret` to `REDACT_FIELDS` in `auditMiddleware.ts`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:266:2. Add `/api/auth/totp/confirm` to `REDACT_PATHS` (the path whose body gets field-level redaction).
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:274:**How to avoid:** Remove the `maxLength={6}` constraint or increase it to handle recovery codes (up to 9 chars for `XXXX-XXXX` format). Backend distinguishes TOTP vs recovery by length/format before trying bcrypt. Alternatively: `maxLength={9}` covers both. Update the `placeholder` to something like `"123456 or recovery code"`.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:276:### Pitfall 7: verifyLocalToken Does Not Reject `totp-enroll` Purpose
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:278:**What goes wrong:** A user who somehow obtains an `enrollToken` (purpose=`totp-enroll`) could use it as a Bearer token on protected API routes if the middleware does not reject it.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:282:**How to avoid:** Add `totp-enroll` to the rejection condition:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:284:if (payload.purpose === 'challenge' || payload.purpose === 'change-password' || payload.purpose === 'totp-enroll') {
