.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:530:| V2 Authentication | Yes | otplib RFC 6238 TOTP; ±1 window; bcrypt recovery codes |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:532:| V4 Access Control | Yes | Admin-only `DELETE /users/:username/totp`; `req.auth.role !== 'admin'` guard |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:534:| V6 Cryptography | Yes | `crypto.randomBytes()` for recovery codes; bcrypt for hashing; never hand-rolled |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:543:| Replay of burned recovery code | Elevation of Privilege | `modifyUsers()` removes burned code atomically under write lock; second use finds no match |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:545:| Enrollment token reuse after confirm | Elevation of Privilege | `enrollToken` has 3-min expiry; `totpEnabled=true` after confirm means re-running confirm yields TOTP mismatch (secret embedded in token, cannot re-enroll with same token) |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:553:| A1 | otplib `authenticator.check()` is sufficient for RFC 6238 compliance with `window: 1` | Standard Stack | Low — widely used, tested library; TOTP spec is simple |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:554:| A2 | Embedding `totpSecret` in the signed `enrollToken` JWT payload is secure for the 3-minute window | Code Examples | Low — JWT is signed with server secret; secret cannot be read by client without HS256 key |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:555:| A3 | `Promise.all` over bcrypt recovery code hashes is fast enough (< 1s wall time) | Common Pitfalls | Low — libuv thread pool handles concurrent bcrypt well in practice |
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:566:   - Recommendation: Hash the code WITH the dash (hash `ABCD-1234`), display with dash for readability, instruct user to type it as shown. This is consistent with how most services handle formatted recovery codes.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:568:2. **LoginPage OTP input: accept recovery codes transparently?**
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:570:   - What's unclear: The current `maxLength={6}` and `tracking-widest text-center text-lg` styling is optimized for 6-digit codes, not 9-char recovery codes.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-RESEARCH.md:571:   - Recommendation: Remove `maxLength` restriction (or set to 9), keep the field type as `text`. The backend handles both formats. Update placeholder text to mention recovery codes.
