.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:124:- [x] SEC-05 requirement satisfied: bcrypt-hashed recovery codes (rounds=12), burned atomically on use, 10 per enrollment
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:126:- [x] Audit trail redacts totpSecret and enrollToken (server/authApi.ts — auditMiddleware sanitizes these fields)
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:141:**1. [Rule 2 - Missing Critical] Added `totpEnabled?: boolean` to ServerUser interface**
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:143:- **Issue:** The plan's task description referenced `u.totpEnabled === true` as a conditional guard on the JSX button, but the `ServerUser` TypeScript interface did not include this field. Without it, TypeScript would flag the property access as an error.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:144:- **Fix:** Added `totpEnabled?: boolean` to `ServerUser` interface — matching the users.json schema added by Plan 02.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:161:No new network endpoints. The `DELETE /api/auth/users/:username/totp` endpoint was introduced in Plan 02 and threat-modeled there. Client-side threat mitigations applied:
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:163:- T-15-26 (spoofing — button shown to unenrolled users): `u.totpEnabled === true` conditional ensures button hidden for unenrolled users
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:178:## Post-Plan Bug Fix: LoginPage totp_enrollment_required handling
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:182:**Root cause:** `LoginPage.handleCredentials` had no explicit branch for `result.error === 'totp_enrollment_required'`. The error fell through to the generic `else` clause and called `setError(t('loginErrorFailed'))`, displaying a confusing "Login failed" banner before TotpEnrollPage rendered.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:184:**Fix:** Added explicit `else if (result.error === 'totp_enrollment_required')` branch that calls `setError('')`. AuthContext has already set `requiresTotpEnrollment=true` which causes AppRoutes to render TotpEnrollPage — no navigation call is needed.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:188:- `completeTotpEnroll` in AuthContext correctly: clears `requiresTotpEnrollment`, clears `pendingEnrollToken`, stores session JWT in sessionStorage, sets token and user state.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:189:- `TotpEnrollPage` → `RecoveryCodesPanel` correctly calls `completeTotpEnroll(token)` from the Continue button, gated behind the "I have saved" checkbox.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:190:- `/api/auth/totp/confirm` returns a full session JWT via `signSessionToken()`, not a partial token.
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:192:**Commit:** b59b3ba — `fix(15): handle totp_enrollment_required in LoginPage, verify complete enrollment flow`
.planning/phases/15-totp-2fa/15-04-SUMMARY.md:194:**Tests:** 16 passed (totpEnrollment.test.ts + totpAdmin.test.ts). `npx tsc --noEmit` clean.
