    45	#### Phase 14: Security Quick Wins & Performance
    46	**Goal**: Production deployments are protected against JWT algorithm confusion and weak secrets; runtime performance is improved and all chart containers are accessible
    47	**Depends on**: Phase 13 (v1.6)
    48	**Requirements**: SEC-01, SEC-02, SEC-03, PERF-01, PERF-02, A11Y-01
    49	**Success Criteria** (what must be TRUE):
    50	  1. All `jwt.verify()` call sites in `authMiddleware.ts` and `authApi.ts` pass `{ algorithms: ['HS256'] }` — a token signed with `alg: none` or RS256 is rejected with 401
    51	  2. On a fresh deployment, `data/cohort-hash-secret.txt` is auto-created at startup; the `audit.cohortHashSecret` fallback value in `settings.yaml` is no longer consulted for that field
    52	  3. A user whose record carries the default migrated password `changeme2025!` is redirected to a forced password-change flow on their next login; they cannot access any other route until the change is complete
    53	  4. `extractPatientCases` processes a 7-center bundle via O(N+M) Map pre-grouping; no `.filter()` loops nested over observations/procedures/conditions remain
    54	  5. FHIR bundles for all configured centers are loaded into `_bundleCache` during server startup, before the first HTTP request arrives
    55	  6. Every Recharts trajectory chart container renders an `aria-label` that names the metric, eye side, and cohort patient count
    56	**Plans**: 3 plans
    57	
    58	Plans:
    59	- [x] 14-01-PLAN.md — JWT algorithm pin (SEC-01) + cohort hash secret auto-generation (SEC-02)
    60	- [x] 14-02-PLAN.md — O(N+M) patient case extraction (PERF-01) + FHIR bundle cache warming (PERF-02)
    61	- [x] 14-03-PLAN.md — Forced password change enforcement backend + frontend (SEC-03) + ARIA chart labels (A11Y-01)
    62	
    63	#### Phase 15: TOTP 2FA
    64	**Goal**: Each user account has its own TOTP secret; the shared static OTP code is retired; users locked out of TOTP have a recovery path
    65	**Depends on**: Phase 14
    66	**Requirements**: SEC-04, SEC-05
    67	**Success Criteria** (what must be TRUE):
    68	  1. A user can enroll TOTP by scanning a QR code in the UI (or entering the manual key); the enrollment is confirmed by entering a valid TOTP code before being activated
    69	  2. After TOTP enrollment, `POST /verify` accepts only a valid RFC 6238 TOTP code (±1 window); the site-wide static `otpCode` from `settings.yaml` is no longer accepted for that user
    70	  3. At enrollment, the user is shown a set of one-time recovery codes; using a valid recovery code against `POST /verify` succeeds exactly once and marks that code as burned in the database
    71	  4. A user who has not yet enrolled TOTP can still authenticate via the existing static OTP fallback (backward-compat transition window)
    72	  5. An admin can reset another user's TOTP enrollment via the admin panel, forcing them back to the pre-enrollment state
    73	**Plans**: 4 plans
    74	
    75	Plans:
    76	- [x] 15-01-PLAN.md — Scaffolding: install otplib+qrcode, extend UserRecord, expand authMiddleware/auditMiddleware, create Wave 0 test stubs
    77	- [x] 15-02-PLAN.md — Backend: /login TOTP gate + /totp/enroll + /totp/confirm + /verify TOTP&recovery + admin DELETE /users/:username/totp
    78	- [x] 15-03-PLAN.md — Frontend enrollment: TotpEnrollPage + RecoveryCodesPanel + AuthContext state + App.tsx gate + LoginPage OTP length + 21 i18n keys
    79	- [x] 15-04-PLAN.md — AdminPage Reset 2FA button + human end-to-end checkpoint
    80	
    81	#### Phase 16: Cross-Cohort Comparison
    82	**Goal**: A researcher can overlay up to 4 saved cohorts on a single trajectory chart to compare outcome trends side by side; individual patient curves are visually subordinate to cohort medians
    83	**Depends on**: Phase 13 (v1.6)
    84	**Requirements**: XCOHORT-01, XCOHORT-02, XCOHORT-03, XCOHORT-04, VIS-04
    85	**Success Criteria** (what must be TRUE):
    86	  1. From the outcomes view, the user can open a cohort selector and pick 1–4 saved cohorts; all selected cohorts render as overlapping series on a single `ComposedChart`
    87	  2. Per-patient lines are suppressed by default in cross-cohort mode; each cohort renders a median line and IQR band using its own color from `COHORT_PALETTES` (4-color categorical set, distinct from the OD/OS palette)
    88	  3. The chart legend shows each cohort's display name and patient count in the format `Cohort A (N=42 patients)`
    89	  4. The URL updates to `?cohorts=id1,id2,...` and loading that URL restores the same cross-cohort selection without user interaction
    90	  5. In single-cohort mode, individual patient curves are rendered at reduced opacity and desaturated color; the median line is overplotted with increased stroke weight and full saturation

