codex
One more security gap surfaced in the dev path: the production `/api/settings` GET strips secrets for non-admins, but the Vite plugin variant returns the raw settings file after only checking that the caller is authenticated. That leaks the global OTP code and cohort hash secret in the environment the project explicitly treats as first-class (`npm run dev`).
